## {{ rule.title }}

IRS Publication 514's treaty re-sourcing worksheet (lines 16-18) uses an *average-rate* method: it computes the U.S. tax burden on the U.S.-source dividend stack as if those dividends were taxed at your overall effective rate, then compares that U.S. tax to the 15 % treaty source-country floor ([DBA-USA Article 10](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf)'s reduced source-country rate). Excess above the floor is what the treaty re-sourcing additional credit can target.

