For 2025:

- U.S.-source dividends from US25-15: **{{ src.us_source_dividends_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Regular tax before credits (US25-09): **{{ rt.regular_tax_before_credits_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Taxable income (US25-08, Form 1040 line 15): **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.taxable_income"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**

[Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) line 16 — U.S. tax on the U.S.-source dividend stack at average rate `regular_tax × (us_source_dividends / taxable_income)`: **{{ lim.us_tax_on_us_source_dividends_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**.

[Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) line 17 — treaty 15 % source-country tax on the same stack: **{{ lim.treaty_minimum_us_tax_on_us_source_dividends_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**.

[Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) line 18 (= line 16 − line 17, floored at zero): **{{ lim.treaty_resourcing_us_limitation_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**. This is the amount of U.S. tax above the treaty floor that the additional credit can chase.

